args: *pant* Is there no end to these fiends?
We need to hurry and finish them off\nbefore they do permanent damage to the\nvillage!
Taaake this! A power most divine!
Allow me to spare you an unhappy ending.
Vile fiends, wreak not your wanton\ndestruction! In grace shall you perish!
I am one of the twelve great dragons,\nDaikokuten! Have at you! Hyaaah!
We can't let this opening go to waste!\nFollow Daikokuten, everyone!
*yawn* So, you finally decide what to do\nwith your traitors?
Exile? Or maybe you'll cut our heads off\nand stick 'em on pikes to deter future\nmutineers?
Yeah, I made a decision—but nothing so\ngrave. I'm going to forgive them.
Whoa. Y'know, there's being a softie,\nand then there's...whatever you are.
Even if it was only a one-time fluke,\nyou're really going to pardon your allies\nfor betraying you? Just like that?
They all threw their weight behind you\nfor my sake, didn't they?
Uh, what? How could you possibly spin it\nso that an uprising is in FAVOR of the guy\nbeing rised-up against?
Because it wasn't a real uprising.\nIt was the Uprising game.
And seeing that it's a game, it's got rules.\nLike ＂act selflessly, and you lose.＂
That means the inverse is true: The game\nrewards you for thinking about yourself.

The only reason why my friends
participated was to send me a message
that it's okay to live my life for my own
sake, too. Am I wrong?
Ding ding ding. You're as sharp as you are\nfaithful to your pals.
There IS one thing I still need to mull over,\nthough. I've never felt that I was\nsmothering my own desires.
But if that's how it came across, then\nI'd like to rely on others more, and not\nhesitate to voice my own wants and needs.

And then everyone lives happily ever after,
huh? Good thing I incited that uprising!
You're welcome! Welp, it's back to sleep
for me then, so good nigh—
I haven't come to a verdict on you yet,\nMitsuhide.
...Mice. And here I thought you'd let it\nslide.
What were you REALLY trying to do?
I told you, didn't I? I wanted to occupy your\nkingdom.
If that were true, surely you wouldn't have\ncome alone.
Maybe it was a trap to get you to let your\nguard down.
Then it would've just been faster for you\nto kill me while my guard was down.
Why would you—someone so famously\naverse to putting in effort—go to all the\ntrouble of laying the groundwork you did?
I'll tell you why: because your goal was\nnever actually to occupy the kingdom,\nbut to play the Uprising game itself.
I really hadn't pegged you as being this\nperceptive. Bravo.
What I don't understand is WHY\nyou wanted to play the game.
I can't come to a verdict on you if I don't\nhave a full picture of the situation.
Game's over, so I guess there's no harm\nin letting it slip. My reason was simple.
It made me angry to see you breaking\nyour back for other people.
Ooh, yeah, hold that pose.\nThe look on your face is priceless.\nI'm serious about the anger, though.
Why did you feel like that?

Because living only to serve others
makes you lose sight of yourself. I figured
you were on your way to becoming an
empty shell—like I was, a long time ago.
It'll be hard for you to picture, I'm sure,\nbut I used to be a real goody two-shoes.
Don't believe me, do you?\nStill, it's the truth.

I was as mousy as they come. Unreliable.
All I ever did was make others worry.
Eventually, my family got together and
educated me on how to be a good leader.
Everything I did was for my parents—\nfor my family. I pushed myself so hard\nthat I even made a soulpact.
But the cost of a soulpact is...
It's all good. I wouldn't be the person I am\nnow if I hadn't become a Wyrmclan leader.
But anyway, once I made that pact,\nI realized I couldn't keep giving my\nlife away in service of others.
We've all only got one chance at this life.\nIt was then that I decided to forge my own\npath.

And when I looked at you, it made me
remember my past—my days spent as an
empty husk. I'll be honest, it set me off.
That's why I decided to meddle a little.

That's the whole truth. Long story short,
you were nothing more than a stand-in
for my own deep-seated trauma.
Knowing that, what's your verdict?
Let your heart be your guide.
That's exactly what I intend to do.
Because you made me realize that\nI shouldn't forget to live for myself\nas well.
My friends' hearts were aching for me.\nThe Uprising game is what made me\nrealize that.
And it's only because of your insight\nthat I've been inspired to change.
So you're saying you'll try to live a little\nmore selfishly than you do now, eh?\nGreedy, this one.
But y'know what? I can chill with that.\nThat's how life ought to be.
Even a prince is a person before he puts\nhis crown on every morning. You've got\nevery right to live for yourself.
I agree. Thanks for making me realize that,\nMitsuhide.
And on that note, I'm gonna partake of\nyour hospitality here a liiittle bit longer.
I thought you said you'd let bygones be\nbygones. After all, we DID just finish\ntalking about living selfishly and all that.
Now, if you'll excuse me, naptime awaits.\nLooking forward to chilling out together,\n{player_name}.
